@himanshug Doesn't this proposed method of solving this effectively eliminate the benefit of multi-threaded executor for submitting tasks?

Somehow we need to preserve the ability to assign tasks to "behaving" workers in a world where some of the workers are misbehaving and taking along time to acknowledge tasks.

If we take a purely parallel approach per worker, such no 2 launches can be in flight at the same time for the same worker, then that could violate the fill capacity contract, which in general would be OK. But there are still corner cases for things like a single worker with ample capacity to launch tasks, but is misbehaving, what is the proper way to handle this? It would appear as if the cluster has capacity, but in fact does not.

@nishantmonu51 The main reason I didn't make it default was that the discussion in https://github.com/metamx/bytebuffer-collections/pull/15 indicated that the RLE containers are not readable by pre 0.5 versions of roaring. Druid updated to 0.5 in 0.8.2 (#1759), so that means bitmaps written with this option won't be readable by Druid 0.8.1 or earlier.

Maybe that's fine?

