@drcrallen  i don't think so, synchronization is only being introduced for 2 operations..
- select a worker using selectorStrategy
- add selected worker to workersWithUnacknowledgedTask
  this is done to ensure that same worker is not given to more than one thread.
  announceTask step still happens in parallel. So, if there was a worker taking long time to ack the task then other threads will continue making progress with other workers. That was the original intention behind #2521

@nishantmonu51  That is true, we can document this caveat in the doc, that when user decides to use more than one thread then fill capacity might not work as expected.

